---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SurfaceTile from "~/components/mdx/SurfaceTile.astro";
import TileGrid from "~/components/mdx/TileGrid.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Feature deep-dives"
  description="Standalone tours of the most interesting parts of the Currnt platform: the AI co-facilitator cron and the 15M-row CRM engine."
>
  <h1>Feature deep-dives</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Two standalone tours of the parts of Currnt that are unusual enough — or
    central enough — to warrant their own page outside the architecture and
    domain documentation. One is operationally critical, one is genuinely
    strange.
  </p>

  <TileGrid columns={2}>
    <SurfaceTile
      href="/features/crm-engine"
      title="The CRM engine"
      kicker="Operations"
    >
      How 15M prospects got into the database, and the rotating SMTP fleet,
      LinkedIn scrapers, and enrichment APIs that kept reaching them. The
      growth motion that bypassed the marketing site.
    </SurfaceTile>
    <SurfaceTile
      href="/features/ai-cofacilitator"
      title="The AI co-facilitator"
      kicker="Strangest cron"
    >
      Every five minutes, a script wakes up, asks GPT to draft promotional
      copy, and posts the result inside selected advisory boards under a
      single privileged author account. End-to-end tour.
    </SurfaceTile>
  </TileGrid>

  <p class="more">
    Other features worth their own page in a future phase: a guided tour of
    Treehouse&apos;s eight pillars from the inside; a detailed dispenserd
    handler-by-handler reference; a screenshot tour of the corporate
    portal&apos;s branding system.
  </p>

  <style>
    .lede {
      color: var(--fg-soft);
      max-width: 65ch;
    }
    .more {
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      padding-top: 1.2rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
